      "content": "that makes sense. but i've been seeing a lot of stuff online saying that originalism is basically just a way for conservative judges to push a specific political agenda under the guise of law. how would a proponent of originalism respond to the critique that it's just a tool for politics rather than a real legal philosophy?",
